Multiple sentinels in the same rule string each resolve independently.
Useful pattern: chaining two cross-module markers on one selector.

  $ cat > a.ml <<EOF
  > [@@@css.bindings [("A.one", "klass-1"); ("A.two", "klass-2")]]
  > let one = CSS.make "klass-1" []
  > let two = CSS.make "klass-2" []
  > EOF

  $ cat > b.ml <<EOF
  > [@@@css ".target.\000A.one\000.\000A.two\000{padding:1rem;}"]
  > [@@@css.refs [("A.one", "b.ml", 1, 0, 5); ("A.two", "b.ml", 1, 0, 5)]]
  > let _ = A.one
  > let _ = A.two
  > EOF

  $ styled-ppx.generate a.ml b.ml
  /* This file is generated by styled-ppx, do not edit manually */
  .target.klass-1.klass-2{padding:1rem;}
